<div style="background-color:lightskyblue;">
<h2>
    WHAT'S WRONG...
</h2>

<h4>Ocean pollution</h4>
<ul>
    <li>Chemiocal and industrial waste</li>
    <li>Oil spills and petroleum waste</li>
    <li>Plastic waste and general litter</li>
</ul>
<br />
<h4>Overfishing</h4>
<p>
    This not only reduces ocean species by directly fishing them towards a lessened population.
    But it also indirectly reducing the food source of other ocean species,
    which in turn begins to affect the life expectancy and population of other sea creatures.
</p>
<br />
<h4>Deep sea mining</h4>
<p>
    Deep sea mining causes destruction to natural landforms in the ocean, disrupts ocean wild life, ruins ocean and sea floors,
    causes debris and waste in the ocean and also produces noise pollution in the ocean
</p>
<br />
<h4>The harm caused by major companies</h4>
<p>
    Besides industry waste, a lot of companies and corporations
    like Nestle and Coca-cola are responsible for a high percentage of plastic-waste in the ocean.
</p>
<br />
<h4>Endangered ocean species</h4>
<p>Let's have a look at a couple: </p>
